! Backfill: Adding `c7` to Existing Tiddlers

When the plugin is installed, the backfill module runs once at startup and assigns a `c7` field to every non-system tiddler that doesn't already have one.

!! How it works

# For each tiddler without a `c7` field, the module generates a UUID v7 using the best available timestamp:
#* `created` field (preferred)
#* `modified` field (fallback)
#* `Date.now()` (last resort)
# A log tiddler [[_log/backfill-c7]] is written with a table of all affected tiddlers
# In ''live'' mode, `$:/config/TimestampDisable` is temporarily set to `yes` so that writing the `c7` field does not change the `modified` date

!! Modes

Configure the mode in [[$:/ControlPanel]] > Settings > WikiLabs > UUID v7, or set the tiddler `$:/config/wikilabs/uuid7/backfill-mode` directly.

|!Mode |!Behaviour |
|''dry-run'' |Generates UUIDs and writes the log, but does ''not'' modify any tiddlers. Use this to preview what would change. This is the default. |
|''live'' |Writes the `c7` field to all tiddlers that need one. |
|''disabled'' |Skips backfill entirely. |

!! Recommended workflow

# Set mode to ''dry-run'' (default) and reload
# Review [[_log/backfill-c7]] — check the tiddler count and timestamp sources
# If satisfied, switch to ''live'' and reload
# After backfill completes, set mode to ''disabled'' to avoid running it on every startup
